ğŸ”· 9 Best PROTEIN Foods for DIABETICS #unitedstates 

Managing diabetes doesnâ€™t mean limiting your mealsâ€”it means choosing smarter, healthier foods that help stabilize blood sugar and support long-term wellness. 
In this video, discover the 9 best high-protein foods for people with diabetes and why these options are essential for improving insulin sensitivity, balancing blood sugar, reducing inflammation, and keeping you full longer. Ideal for type 2 diabetes, prediabetes, and anyone seeking stable energy and healthier eating.

ğŸŸ¢ Healthy Protein Sources for Diabetes
âœ… Salmon
Rich in omega-3s, lean protein, and naturally carb-free, salmon helps improve insulin sensitivity, support blood sugar control, reduce inflammation, and lower the risk of cardiovascular complications and high blood pressureâ€”conditions commonly associated with diabetes.

âœ… Chicken Breast
High in protein, low in carbs and fat, it helps you stay full longer, reduces cravings, and prevents sudden blood sugar spikes.

âœ… Eggs
Packed with protein that slows sugar absorption, eggs have a glycemic index of 0 and provide healthy fats that keep you full and help prevent rapid increases in blood glucose. Choose boiled or steamed preparation.

âœ… Greek Yogurt
High in protein, low in sugar, and rich in probiotics, Greek yogurt helps slow carbohydrate absorption, prolong satiety, reduce inflammation, and improve blood sugar control.

âœ… Tofu
Low glycemic index, rich in protein and isoflavones. Tofu slows sugar absorption, reduces post-meal spikes, improves insulin sensitivity, and helps maintain stable glucose levels.

âœ… Lentils
Low-GI, rich in soluble fiber and plant-based protein, lentils slow digestion and sugar absorption, preventing blood sugar spikes after meals.

âœ… Almonds
Contain fiber, protein, healthy fats (omega-3 & omega-6), and plenty of magnesiumâ€”all of which slow sugar absorption, improve insulin sensitivity, and reduce post-meal blood sugar surges.

âœ… Cottage Cheese
(Cottage cheese, ricotta)
 High in protein and fat with a low GI, it slows carbohydrate absorption, increases satiety, and reduces cravings for sweets. Choose low-fat, low-sugar, low-sodium options and eat in moderation.

âœ… Quinoa
Low glycemic index, high in fiber, complete high-quality protein (with all essential amino acids), magnesium, and antioxidants. Quinoa helps slow sugar absorption, improve insulin sensitivity, and may support prevention of type 2 diabetes more effectively than many common grains.

ğŸ”· Cooking Tips
âœ”ï¸ Recommended: Steaming, boiling, baking, grilling, or pan-searing with minimal oil.
 âœ”ï¸ Avoid: Deep-frying and processed meats (sausages, cured meats).
â‡ï¸ Closing
Take control of your healthâ€”start adding these high-protein, diabetes-friendly foods to your daily meals and feel the difference in your energy, blood sugar, and overall well-being.

A quick recipe 
Cut 3 tomatoes in halves.
Add 2 tbsp oil & Place the tomato halves face down in the pan.
Then add 5 garlic and 1 chopped onion and cook until soft.
Remove the tomatoes skin and mash it along with garlic and onions.
Now add 1 tbsp pepper powder, 1 tbsp chilli powder, salt and 1/2 cup fresh cream.
Cook for 2 min & add 1 cup cooked pasta, mixed herbs, pasta water 1/4 cup and cook for 5 min.
Add grated cheese and mix gently.
Serve it hot.

Students destroying and protesting at VIT Bhopal College
description:
#facts #amazingfacts #knowledge 


The recent VIT Bhopal student protest began after hundreds of students fell sick due to a major jaundice outbreak on campus, which they believe was caused by contaminated drinking water and unhygienic hostel food. Students claimed that complaints about foul-smelling water, poor sanitation, and inadequate medical facilities had been ignored for months. Tension escalated when videos surfaced allegedly showing hostel staff mistreating students who had raised these issues. On the night of the protest, nearly 4,000 students gathered, and the situation turned violentâ€”vehicles, including buses and an ambulance, were vandalised or torched, and parts of the administration area were damaged. The university temporarily shut down the campus and declared holidays, while the Madhya Pradesh government issued notices to the institute and launched an investigation. Water testing later revealed contamination in multiple points on campus. Although rumours circulated online about student deaths, the administration officially denied any fatalities. The incident has now turned into a major debate about student safety, infrastructure quality, and accountability in private universities.

title: The One Protein-Rich Salad Youâ€™ll Want Every Single Day
description:
Save this filling, crunchy & protein-rich recipe to make later!ğŸ¥— 

Makes: 2 | Time: 20 mins â±ï¸

ğŸŸ¢ Preparation
Soak Â¼ cup kala chana in water overnight.
Soak Â¼ cup sunflower seeds for 6 hours.

ğŸŸ¢ Ingredients

For Chana

Â¼ cup kala chana, soaked
Â¼ tsp rock salt
Â½ cup water

For Dressing

Â¼ cup makhana, roasted
Â¼ cup sunflower seeds, soaked
2 tbsp chopped coriander leaves
5 mint leaves
1 small green chili
1 tbsp lemon juice
Â¾ tsp rock salt
Â¼ cup water

Veggies

Â¾ cup chopped tomato
Â¾ cup chopped cucumber
Â¾ cup chopped capsicum

Topping

2 tbsp roasted sunflower seeds

1 tsp chopped coriander leaves

ğŸŸ¢ Method

1. Heat a pressure cooker and add soaked kala chana, rock salt and water. Cook for 4 whistles on medium flame, then 2 on low flame.

2. Let the steam release and transfer the cooked chana to a bowl.

3. Blend all dressing ingredients until smooth.

4. In a mixing bowl, add the veggies, cooked chana and dressing. Toss well.

5. Top with roasted sunflower seeds and coriander, and serve fresh!

Tip: Chill the salad for 15 minutes before serving for an even better crunch and flavor.

No Bake Christmas Coconut Lasagna
description:
Recipe: No-Bake Christmas Coconut Lasagna
Ingredients:
For the Crust:
2 cups crushed vanilla wafer cookies (Nilla Wafers) or shortbread cookies
1/2 cup unsalted butter, melted
For the Coconut Cheesecake Layer:
1 (8 oz) package cream cheese, softened
1 cup powdered sugar
1 teaspoon coconut extract
1 (8 oz) tub whipped topping (Cool Whip), thawed (divided use)
For the Pudding Layer:
2 packages (3.4 oz each) instant coconut cream pudding mix
2 Â¾ cups cold milk
For the Topping:
Remaining whipped topping
1 Â½ cups sweetened shredded coconut
Red and green holiday sprinkles
Instructions:
Make the Crust: In a medium bowl, combine the crushed vanilla wafers and melted butter. Press the mixture firmly into the bottom of a 9x13 inch baking dish. Place in the freezer for 10 minutes to set.
Make Cheesecake Layer: In a large bowl, beat the softened cream cheese, powdered sugar, and coconut extract until smooth and creamy. Gently fold in 1 cup of the whipped topping. Spread this mixture carefully over the chilled crust.
Make Pudding Layer: In another bowl, whisk together the instant pudding mixes and cold milk for 2 minutes until it begins to thicken. Spread the pudding layer over the cream cheese layer.
Top: Spread the remaining whipped topping over the pudding layer.
Garnish: Sprinkle the shredded coconut generously over the top to look like snow. Add the red and green sprinkles for a festive touch.
Chill: Refrigerate for at least 4 hours (or overnight) to allow the layers to set and the crust to soften slightly.
Serve: Cut into a square slice and serve cold.

title: 15-Minute Vegetarian Dinner Recipe (Easy Bean Recipe!) #shorts
description:
Now, these are the SEXIEST white beans youâ€™ll ever try! It takes only 2 cans of cannellini beans, and 15 minutes or less to make this delicious white beans recipe with garlic, Parmesan, and cherry tomatoes. Serve it as an easy meatless dinner with your favorite crusty bread or as a side.

How to make this bean recipe: 
â–¢3 to 4 garlic cloves, minced
â–¢Extra virgin olive oil
â–¢2 15-ounce cans cannellini beans, drained
â–¢1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved
â–¢Kosher salt and black pepper
â–¢1 teaspoon Aleppo pepper
â–¢Â½ teaspoon cumin
â–¢1 cup chopped fresh parsley
â–¢Â¼ to 1/3 cup shaved Parmesan cheese
â–¢1/4 cup grated Pecorino Romano
â–¢Juice of half a lemon

1. In a large pan, warm 2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil over medium heat. Add the garlic and cook briefly, tossing regularly, until just golden.
2. Add the cannellini beans and Â½ cup water. Season with kosher salt, black pepper, and the spices. 3. Add the tomatoes. Cook, stirring occasionally until warmed through (about 10 minutes)
Stir in the parsley, cheese, and lemon juice.
4. Finish with a generous drizzle of extra virgin olive oil. Serve immediately with pita or your favorite crusty bread.

title: Zingy Chicken Power Bowl - 476 calories & 54g protein
description:
Zingy Chicken Power Bowl: 476 cals, 54g protein

Iâ€™ve lost over 100 pounds, and the biggest game changer was this: I started making high protein, low carb meals and sauces that actually taste GOOD.

Keeping things ridiculously simple, bold, and satisfying has been the secret. This bowl is all of that: packed with about 50g of protein, low in carbs, and full of flavor. I used my Kaizen high protein rice (its got 20g protein, just 6g net carbs per serving), but you can use whatever you like: regular rice, brown rice, or even quinoa work just fine. 

Hereâ€™s how I made it: (makes 4 servings)

1.Start with the chicken. I used 1.5lbs chicken (you can use your favorite cut). Drizzle with 1 tbsp olive oil, then season with 1 tbsp each of onion powder, garlic powder, and paprika, 2 tsp ground pepper, and a generous couple pinches of salt.

2.Air fry, bake, or sear and finish in the oven at 400F for 37 to 40 minutes or until cooked through.

3.While the chicken cooks, prepare 4 servings of Rice according to instructions. I used my @kaizenfoodco protein rice here, but use what you like.

4.Make the salad: Slice 4 Persian cucumbers into thin half moons, quarter a big handful of cherry tomatoes, finely dice half a red onion, and chop a handful of fresh mint or lemon basil. Add the zest of a lemon, juice of a lemon, 2 tbsp olive oil, and season with salt and pepper. Toss well, taste and adjust.

5.For the sauce: In a food processor, blend 1/2 cup Greek yogurt, 2 tbsp mayo, 1 tbsp olive oil, juice of 3 limes, 1 garlic clove, a big handful of basil and chives (2 to 3 tbsp each), salt and pepper. Add 1 to 2 tbsp cold water to thin if needed!

6.Plate it up: Add rice, a few spoonfuls of salad, sliced or chopped chicken, and a few tablespoons of the basil-chive sauce. Finish with crumbled feta (about 1/4 oz per serving), chili flakes, more herbs & sesame seeds

It doesnâ€™t feel like a â€œhealthyâ€ mealâ€¦ it just tastes really, really good


ENJOY!

description:
Crockpot Chicken Soup
Ingredients
2 lbs boneless, skinless chicken thighs 1 packet mild taco seasoning (Simply Organic) 1 jar mild salsa
(16 oz) 1 can black beans, drained and rinsed 1 can red kidney beans, drained and rinsed 1 can diced
tomatoes (with juices) 1 bag frozen corn (about 2 cups) 2 cups chicken stock
Combine & Cover and cook on LOW for 6â€“8 hours or HIGH for 3â€“4 hours.

Dump & Go Pulled BBQ Chicken
Ingredients
2 lbs boneless, skinless chicken thighs or breasts 1 medium onion, sliced 1 bottle BBQ sauce (about 2
cups) 2â€“3 tbsp honey 1 tsp garlic powder 1 tsp salt 1/2 tsp black pepper
Instructions
Combine and cook on low for 6â€“7 hours or HIGH for 3â€“4 hours. Add extra BBQ sauce before serving for saucier pulled chicken. Delicious topped with coleslaw!

Chuck Roast Tacos
Ingredients
3â€“4 lbs chuck roast salt & 1 l packet Siete taco seasoning, almond flour tortillas (Siete
brand) 1 can beans (black or pinto), warmed Shredded cheese Lettuce, chopped Seed of Change organic Spanish rice (for serving)
Instructions
Preheat oven to 325Â°F. Season chuck roast generously with salt and Siete taco seasoning.
Cook 1 hour per lb. Of roast doesnâ€™t shred easily do another 30 min, until meat is tender and shreds
easily

Sweet Balls (Crockpot BBQ Jelly Meatballs)
Ingredients
1 bag frozen Italian-style meatballs
1.5 cups Sweet Baby Rayâ€™s Honey BBQ Sauce
1.5 cups grape jelly (Smuckerâ€™s Natural or similar)

Instructions
Place frozen meatballs into the crockpot. Add BBQ sauce and grape jelly on top. Stir to coat meatballs evenly.
Cover and cook on LOW for 4 hours or HIGH for 2 hours, until meatballs are heated through and sauce is bubbly.
Stir before serving and enjoy warm.

Perfect as a party appetizer or served over rice for a quick meal.

â¸»

Lemon Parmesan Pasta with Chicken Cutlets
Ingredients
1 lb chicken cutlets (or thinly sliced chicken breasts)
1 cup flour
2 eggs, beaten
1 cup gluten-free panko or Italian bread crumbs
1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese
Salt and pepper, to taste
1 lb gluten-free spaghetti (brown rice pasta)
1 jar Carbone lemon pasta sauce

Instructions
Set up a breading station with three bowls: flour in one, beaten eggs in the second, and a mixture of bread crumbs, Parmesan, salt, and pepper in the third.

Dredge chicken cutlets in flour, dip in egg, then coat in breadcrumb mixture.

Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. Cook chicken cutlets 3â€“4 minutes per side until golden brown and cooked through. Set aside.

Meanwhile, cook spaghetti according to package instructions.

Serve chicken cutlets alongside lemon pasta with marinara on the side or drizzled over.

title: Rolled (Twisted) Baklava / Rulo baklava
description:
Rolled (Twisted) Baklava Recipe

Ingredients:

* 30 sheets of phyllo dough (for baklava)
* 300 g melted butter (clarified â€“ foam removed)
* 2 cups crushed hazelnuts, walnuts, or pistachios (for the filling)

For the syrup:

* 3 cups granulated sugar
* 2 cups water
* 1/4 lemon (juice or slice)

To Prepare the Syrup:

1. Place the sugar, lemon, and water in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
2. Once it starts boiling, reduce to medium heat and simmer for about 15 minutes.
3. Remove from heat and let it cool completely.

To Prepare the Baklava:

1. Use the phyllo sheets in pairs (two at a time).
2. Lay two sheets on top of each other and place a rolling pin across the edge.
3. Place the filling along the rolling pin and roll up the phyllo. Lightly brush the edge with some butter to seal.
4. Gather the dough from both ends toward the center to create the twisted shape.
5. Carefully remove the rolling pin and transfer the twisted roll to a baking tray.
6. Repeat the process with all the phyllo sheets and arrange them in the tray.
7. Cut the rolls into slices using a sharp knife.
8. Pour the melted, clarified butter evenly over the baklava.

Baking:

1. Bake in a preheated oven at 200Â°C (390Â°F) for 10 minutes.
2. Then lower the temperature to 180Â°C (355Â°F) and bake for another 30 minutes.
3. Once out of the oven, pour the cooled syrup over the hot baklava.

Enjoy!

description:
ğŸ¥¦ High-Protein Broccoli Feta Soup

This high protein broccoli feta soup is as good as it gets. Itâ€™s got roasted broccoli & feta as the star ingredients, with two of my favorite protein hacks cottage cheese and bone broth making it high protein and super filling. Itâ€™s perfect for meal prep, lunch, or a dinner that leaves you full without feeling heavy. The roasted broccoli comes out almost a little nutty, and itâ€™s the perfect texture when itâ€™s all blended.

Total (whole recipe):
984 calories Â· 78g protein

Per serving (4 servings):
246 calories Â· 19.5g protein Â· 10g carbs

Ingredients:

5 cups (450g) broccoli florets, cut small so they roast evenly
2 cups baby spinach
1 small yellow onion, quartered
4 garlic cloves, peeled
1 tbsp olive oil
3 cups bone broth (I used K&F)
1/2 cup cottage cheese
6oz feta cheese (reserve a little for topping)
Zest and juice of Â½ large lemon
1 tsp dried oregano
1/2 tsp chili flakes (plus extra for garnish)
Salt and pepper to taste
Optional: Fresh dill and finely shredded Parmesan or Manchego for garnish

Hereâ€™s how I made it:

1ï¸âƒ£ Preheat oven to 415Â°F

2ï¸âƒ£ Cut the broccoli into small florets so it roasts evenly and cooks faster.

3ï¸âƒ£ Toss broccoli, onion, and garlic with olive oil, oregano, chili flakes, salt, and pepper. Tuck the feta in the corner. Roast for 28â€“30 mins until golden and slightly crisp at the edges.

4ï¸âƒ£ Add roasted veggies to a blender with bone broth, spinach, cottage cheese, lemon zest, and juice. Blend until smooth and creamy.

5ï¸âƒ£ Warm through in a pot, taste and adjust seasoning, then garnish with fresh dill, chili flakes, and finely shredded Parmesan or Manchego.

If you make it, be sure to let me know on SHREDHAPPENS! 

Enjoy!
